When I found out that St. Louis is known for gooey butter cake, I knew we had to try it. That's Anthony's ice cream favorite flavor at Jeni's, so the real thing had to be great.  Covid-19: we were able to order and pay over the phone. When we got there, they brought our order out to the car for us.  This place boasts 73 flavors so it seemed like a great place to try it. That's misleading though because they're only available for shipping online. In the store, they have 7 flavors (and none of their seasonal ones).  We had to get a slice of the traditional and then we got the only other non-chocolate flavor they had which was white chocolate raspberry.  The traditional is where it's at. It was amazing. It's probably one of my favorite desserts and now I'm wondering where I can find it in Charlotte (if you know, hit me up).  The white chocolate raspberry was good, but I think the added flavor took away from the gooey butter cake flavor instead of enhancing it. I tasted the white chocolate but we didn't taste any raspberry.  If you're in St. Louis, you need to try some gooey butter cake!

We traveled from Wisconsin to St. Louis for a baseball tournament this past weekend.  Several in our party had heard about the gooey buttercake and that Park Avenue Coffee was the best.  After a trip to the top of the Gateway Arch, we made the lengthy trek to partake.  The cake was exceptional and many of us in our party sampled several flavors.  So the cake would receive five stars.  It was the service we had a problem with.  The young woman behind the counter had an exceptionally poor attitude and appeared to be angry at the world.  Lips were pursed, head tilted to the side, strained tone in her voice and slamming trays down hastily.  Note that this carried on from our group's arrival to the end.  My family was first to be served and we were nothing other than courteous and respectful.  All eighteen of us experienced this displeasure.  I did not catch her name (and would have been afraid to ask).  But if the owner reads this review, the young women has blond hair, shaved on the sides.  She ought to be let go as the "best gooey buttercake" honor is in jeopardy with her in your midst.
